<TITLE> Rain, flash floods deluge Bangladesh </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 12 (bdnews24.com)Rain and flash floods have swept much of the country, bursting the banks of rivers. In Bandarban, heavy rain and flash flooding has caused the rivers Matamuhuri and Sangu to overflow, washing away about 2,000 houses and claiming at least two livesBaby Barua, 7, and her grandmother Parul Barua, 55. Rasheduzzaman, the met office duty officer, told bdnews24.com that the monsoon wind was gradually losing strengtha lull that would continue for two more days. However the Water Development Board has issued further flood warnings. Seaports were asked to keep hoisting local cautionary signal No. 3 for Tuesday. Southern river ports are maintaining cautionary signal No. 2. Flash floods streaming from the northeast Indian Garo and Khasi hills inundated low-lying areas, bordering India, including northern Bishwambharpur, Tahirpur and Doarabazar The Surma river flows above danger level and the Kushiara has also registered an increase. Many areas in the district of Sunamganj are waterlogged. Kamalganj in Moulvibazar has also gone under water due to flash floods. The Jamuna flood protection embankment suffered breaches at Madarganj in Jamalpur, inundating at least 20 villages. Lama, Rowangchhari, Ruma and Thanchi upazilas have suffered road and telecommunication difficulties following the monsoon flooding. bdnews2
